  Chapter(13, "Write short notes on:",
      "Abacus:\n‚Ä¢ It is developed by Chinese in 3000 B.C.\n‚Ä¢  It is still used by millions of people throughout Asia.\n‚Ä¢ It has rectangular wooden frame with rods carrying round beads.\n\nENIAC:\n‚Ä¢	Developed by John Mauchly and John Eckert in 1946.\n‚Ä¢	Known as Electronic Numerical Integrator and Calculator.\n‚Ä¢	This machine could discriminate the sign of number, compare quantities for equality, add, subtract, multiply, divide and extract square roots.\n‚Ä¢	It consists of 18000 vacuum tubes with 160KW electricity and weight 30 tons.\n\nEDVAC:\n‚Ä¢	Designed by John William Mauchly and John Presper Eckert jr.in 1946.\n‚Ä¢	Known as Electronic Discrete Variable Automatic Computer.\n‚Ä¢	It included a stored program, a central processor and a memory for both data and programs.\n‚Ä¢	It consists of approximately 4000 vacuum tubes.\n‚Ä¢	It consumed 56 Kilowatts of electric power."),
  Chapter(
      14,
